Project: Splitter Pay for Klearly
Author: Newton Tugadi

Requirement: 
    Ensure you have [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/) installed on your machine before running or testing the script. You can verify if Node.js is installed by running the following command in your terminal:

  ```bash
  node -v

Front End Tools:

    1. Vite React JS / Typescript
    2. Axios
    3. ContextAPI and useReducer for states management

Back End:

    1. NodeJS
    2. Express
    3. MongoDB (Atlas)
    4. Mongoose


Setup (For testing purposes only):

    1. Clone this repository: open your terminal and type: git git@github.com:newtonboy75/splitter_pay.git
    2. cd to backend, type: npm install, please wait for all dependencies to be installed, .env file sent through email
    3. type: npm run dev
    4. cd to frontend, type: npm install
    5. type: npm run build
    6. type: npm run preview
    7. on your browser, go to http://localhost:4173/

Demo on how to use: 

   Link to the screen recording: https://drive.google.com/file/d/1y4jUhr-dM8XM9UstwOcL75Zj3pzKcnvs/view?usp=sharing


Thank you and looking forward to talking to you!!!
    